## Architecture Patterns

Codebase architecture docs live in `docs/current/codebase/`. Two rules:
1. Before debugging a system-level problem, check for an existing doc.
2. After resolving a problem requiring non-obvious understanding, add or update a doc.

**Service layer pattern**: UI calls service (no logic in UI) → service contains all business logic. Services must NOT import UI components; accept callbacks for dialogs.

**Index file requirements**: Index files at root (`nodes-index.yaml`, `parameters-index.yaml`). Data files in subdirectories. IDB uses workspace-prefixed IDs.

---

## Debugging Discipline

**Full details**: `docs/current/codebase/DEBUGGING_DISCIPLINE.md`

**Key rules kept here because they are the most violated**:

- **No "Not My Problem" dismissals**: every issue you encounter is yours to investigate, regardless of who caused it. Investigate, report, propose action.
- **Root-Cause Gate**: Can you name the root cause in one sentence with a "because"? If not, you are not ready to write code.
- **Recurring defect = multiple code paths**: grep ALL call sites, verify fix applies to ALL, consolidate into ONE canonical function.
- **Broken infrastructure is a blocking issue**: devtools, log streams, test harnesses — fix properly or escalate. No silent workarounds.
- **NEVER blame server staleness without proof (HARD BLOCK)**. Before saying "the server may not have restarted" or "HMR may not have picked up the change", run `scripts/dev-server-check.sh <file-you-edited>`. If it says FRESH, **the problem is your code** — investigate the logic. If it says STALE, check the server terminal pane for syntax/import errors that blocked the reload. See `docs/current/codebase/DEV_ENVIRONMENT_AND_HMR.md` for details.

---

## Testing and Build

**Full standards**: `docs/current/codebase/TESTING_STANDARDS.md`

- **Run relevant tests only**: `cd graph-editor && npm test -- --run path/to/file.test.ts` or `pytest tests/specific_test.py` (venv first)
- **NEVER use `head`, `tail`, or any truncation on test/build output.** This is NON-NEGOTIABLE.
- **Do NOT run `npm run build`** unless explicitly instructed.

---

## Change Checklist

**Full checklist**: `docs/current/codebase/CHANGE_CHECKLIST.md`

Before reporting done: run relevant tests (write new ones if needed), check all call sites, verify state in all affected layers, test the "already clean" case, state what you verified and how.

---

## Documentation Structure

**Full details**: `docs/current/codebase/DOCUMENTATION_STRUCTURE.md`

- User-facing: `graph-editor/public/docs/`
- Technical: `docs/current/` (active), `docs/archive/` (historical)
- Active docs default to `docs/current/` root — design specs, investigation records, open issues, pending plans
- Codebase reference: `docs/current/codebase/` — curated, indexed library of how the app works. NOT a dumping ground.
- Contexts feature project: `docs/current/project-contexts/` — design docs for the "contexts" app feature ONLY. Not a general bucket.
- Handover notes: `docs/current/handover/` — read if one exists for your work area
- Always check relevant docs BEFORE making changes

---

## Code Surface Area

- **NO backward compatibility shims**, deprecated aliases, "just in case" code, or legacy wrappers.
- When renaming/refactoring: make the change cleanly, update all references, delete old code entirely.

## Documentation Standards

**Implementation plans are PROSE ONLY** — no code snippets, pseudo-code, test assertions, or function signatures.

## Remember

> "Menus are access points. Services are logic. Tests are proof."
